dynGuiComponents.name: android.widget.TextView
dynGuiComponents.text:
Open Map is a demo application for the osmdroid software library. It's purpose is to show how to use the various functions and capabilities of osmdroid. 
 
osmdroid is a (almost) full/free replacement for Android's MapView (v1 API) class. It also includes a modular tile provider system with support for numerous online and offline tile sources and overlay support with built-in overlays for plotting icons, tracking location, and drawing shapes.
 
Good news: It's free and open source!
 
We rely on volunteers to keep osmdroid going and welcome contributions of all types.

dynGuiComponents.name: android.widget.TextView
dynGuiComponents.text: osmdroid needs some permissions to get going. It works in most cases without them, but not all examples will function correctly.

dynGuiComponents.name: android.widget.TextView
dynGuiComponents.text: This is needed to place an icon on the map where this device is located.

dynGuiComponents.name: android.widget.TextView
dynGuiComponents.text: osmdroid provides access to online maps from a variety of sources. Online maps are chopped up into millions of small images called tiles. To save you bandwidth, osmdroid caches those tiles on your device as they are downloaded. Without this permission, tiles are stored in this application's prviate storage area, typically on the devices internal storage. With this permission, you can store the cache at any writable location, such as an sdcard. When stored on the sdcard, other apps that use osmdroid will share the same cache which saves you space on your device.

dynGuiComponents.name: android.widget.TextView
dynGuiComponents.text: Almost there! We just wanted to confirm that that location we selected automatically, is ok with you storing the map tile cache

dynGuiComponents.name: android.widget.TextView
dynGuiComponents.text: This demo application provides access to online map source. When used on a metered network, this may be result in data charges.  The Cache Manager can use a LOT of data. Use your own judgement. We're not responsible for data overages or charges.

dynGuiComponents.name: android.widget.TextView
dynGuiComponents.text:
This demo application provides access to Open Street Map map tiles by default.

 You are free to copy, distribute, transmit and adapt our data, as long as you credit OpenStreetMap and its contributors. If you alter or build upon our data, you may distribute the result only under the same licence. The full legal code explains your rights and responsibilities. 

 The cartography in our map tiles, and our documentation, are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 2.0 license (CC BY-SA). 

 More information is available at http://www.openstreetmaps.org

dynGuiComponents.name: android.widget.TextView
dynGuiComponents.text:
This demo application provides access to Mapsforge based tiles. Osmdroid and OpenMap are open source, Apache Software Foundation 2.0 Licensed projects. Mapsforge is LGPL v3. If you use Mapsforge in your project, you should understand the terms of the license and adhere to it. Mapforge is not required for osmdroid to function.

 More information is available at https://github.com/mapsforge/mapsforge
